### Implement middleware with Fastify raw request/response objects

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/performance.md

TypeScript and JavaScript middleware implementation for NestJS with Fastify. Middleware functions receive raw req and res objects from Fastify instead of wrappers. The example shows a LoggerMiddleware class implementing NestMiddleware with proper type annotations for FastifyRequest and FastifyReply raw objects.

```typescript
import { Injectable, NestMiddleware } from '@nestjs/common';
import { FastifyRequest, FastifyReply } from 'fastify';

@Injectable()
export class LoggerMiddleware implements NestMiddleware {
  use(req: FastifyRequest['raw'], res: FastifyReply['raw'], next: () => void) {
    console.log('Request...');
    next();
  }
}
```

```javascript
import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';

@Injectable()
export class LoggerMiddleware {
  use(req, res, next) {
    console.log('Request...');
    next();
  }
}
```

