### Use Fastify route config with @RouteConfig decorator

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/performance.md

TypeScript code demonstrating the @RouteConfig() decorator from @nestjs/platform-fastify. This allows setting Fastify-specific route configuration properties. Example shows defining output data in route config and accessing it via req.routeConfig.

```typescript
@RouteConfig({ output: 'hello world' })
@Get()
index(@Req() req) {
  return req.routeConfig.output;
}
