### Listen to Queue Active Event in NestJS Bull

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/queues.md

Demonstrates how to use the @OnQueueActive() decorator to listen for events when a job enters the active state in a Bull queue. The handler receives the Job object and logs processing information including job ID, name, and data.

```typescript
import { Processor, Process, OnQueueActive } from '@nestjs/bull';
import { Job } from 'bull';

@Processor('audio')
export class AudioConsumer {

  @OnQueueActive()
  onActive(job: Job) {
    console.log(
      `Processing job ${job.id} of type ${job.name} with data ${job.data}...`,
    );
  }
}
```

