### ClientsModule.registerAsync() - Asynchronous Configuration

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/microservices/basics.md

Register ClientProxy instances with asynchronous configuration when you need to fetch transporter configuration from services like ConfigService or perform async setup operations.

```APIDOC
## ClientsModule.registerAsync()

### Description
Registers microservice client instances with asynchronous configuration. This approach is useful when configuration needs to be fetched from external services or when async initialization is required.

### Method
Static method on ClientsModule

### Usage Location
Module imports array

### Parameters
#### Configuration Array Object
- **imports** (array) - Optional - Modules to import (e.g., ConfigModule)
- **name** (string | symbol) - Required - Injection token for the ClientProxy instance
- **useFactory** (async function) - Required - Factory function that returns transport options
- **inject** (array) - Required - Services to inject into the factory function

### Request Example
```typescript
@Module({
  imports: [
    ClientsModule.registerAsync([
      {
        imports: [ConfigModule],
        name: 'MATH_SERVICE',
        useFactory: async (configService: ConfigService) => ({
          transport: Transport.TCP,
          options: {
            url: configService.get('URL'),
          },
        }),
        inject: [ConfigService],
      },
    ]),
  ],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

### Injection Example
```typescript
constructor(
  @Inject('MATH_SERVICE') private client: ClientProxy,
) {}
```

### Notes
- Import from '@nestjs/microservices' package
- Allows dynamic configuration based on services
- Supports asynchronous initialization operations
```

