### Enable auto-caching for a NestJS controller

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/caching.md

Applies the `CacheInterceptor` to a specific NestJS controller using the `@UseInterceptors` decorator. This automatically caches responses for `GET` endpoints defined within that particular controller, improving performance.

```typescript
@Controller()
@UseInterceptors(CacheInterceptor)
export class AppController {
  @Get()
  findAll(): string[] {
    return [];
  }
}
```

