### Run a NestJS standalone application for benchmarking

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/faq/serverless.md

This TypeScript snippet demonstrates how to create a NestJS application context without an HTTP server, often referred to as a standalone application. It's useful for benchmarking the core bootstrap time of NestJS itself, independent of network listener overhead, and showcases interaction with a service.

```typescript
import { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core';
import { AppModule } from './app.module';
import { AppService } from './app.service';

async function bootstrap() {
  const app = await NestFactory.createApplicationContext(AppModule, {
    logger: ['error'],
  });
  console.log(app.get(AppService).getHello());
}
bootstrap();
```

