### Implement Partial Registration with forFeature() in NestJS

Source: https://github.com/nestjs/docs.nestjs.com/blob/master/content/techniques/configuration.md

Use ConfigModule.forFeature() in feature modules to perform partial registration of feature-specific configurations. This allows configurations to be loaded only where needed, keeping feature modules independent and reducing root module complexity.

```typescript
import databaseConfig from './config/database.config';

@Module({
  imports: [ConfigModule.forFeature(databaseConfig)],
})
export class DatabaseModule {}
```

